  "prompt": "Can Indians work for NASA?",
  "response": "Yes, Indians can work for NASA, but there are specific requirements and restrictions. Generally, to work for NASA as a civil servant, you must be a U.S. citizen due to federal employment laws. However, NASA also collaborates with international space agencies and has opportunities for foreign nationals through specific programs, internships, or roles that may be contracted out to private companies working with NASA. Additionally, students and professionals can engage with NASA through various academic partnerships and exchange programs. It is important for interested individuals to check specific job listings and NASA\u2019s official website for opportunities and eligibility criteria.",
